The paper focuses on developing a next-generation DSP architecture for dense linear algebra kernels, which involves exploiting fine-grain ordered parallelism. This topic falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and parallel and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses data structures and algorithms for efficient memory access and reuse, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hardware specialization for dataflow criticality, which falls under the category of performance analysis and design aids (cs.PF) and control systems (cs.SY).
